&lt;p&gt;Total Candidates&amp;nbsp;in line are&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;17 (candidate above chetan) + 14 (candidate below chetan) = 31&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;31 + 1 = 32 (Including chetan)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Hence, The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;32&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The logic followed here is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Let the number of girls be G and the number of boys be B.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;According to the given information:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;B = 2G&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;B + G = 66&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Substituting B = 2G into the second equation:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;2G + G = 66&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;3G = 66&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;G = 66 / 3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;G = 22&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Therefore, the number of girls is 22 and the number of boys is 44.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Pavithra is ranked 18th from the top, and there are 11 boys ahead of her.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;So, the number of girls ahead of Pavithra = 18 - 11 - 1 = 6 (since Pavithra is also a girl).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Total number of girls = 22&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Number of girls after Pavithra = 22 - 7 = 15&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Option 2&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

